v1.4.19: Sync fixes, attachments moved, form improvements, backup onboarding

Sync:
- httpPost now follows HTTP redirects (301/302/307/308) and checks status codes
- Increased sync timeout from 10s to 30s to prevent timeouts with larger batches
- Push guards against race condition: checks sync_version before clearing dirty flag
- Better error logging for push/pull failures

Form:
- Attachments consolidated to end of record near Invoice section with clear guidance
- Legacy per-section attachments auto-migrated to unified location
- Case assessment changed to dropdown (Strong/Medium/Weak/N/A) with reasoning box
- Client instructions: new larger text box above summary
- Clothing/shoes/phone seized: conditional what and notes fields when Yes
- Offence dates: clearer Start date / End date labels for Between qualifier
- Dropdown defaults set to N/A where appropriate

Settings and onboarding:
- First-launch wizard: 2-step setup with backup destination selection
- Backup summary in settings shows Local, Off-site, and AWS Cloud status
- Detect cloud folders button (OneDrive, Dropbox, Google Drive, iCloud)

Performance:
- Form change handlers update only the changed field inline
- Full DOM collection deferred via debounced scheduleCollect
